    "Body": " Marketing Lead loyyal corporation - San Francisco, CA Apply Now Job Details Full-time Full Job Description Loyyal Corporation Loyyal is the Internet of Loyalty, on a mission to connect the largest loyalty programs across the world. Leveraging blockchain and smart contract technology, we provide a common ground for interoperability, accelerate the speed at which customers can earn and redeem value, give tools to programs to fine-tune incentivization, and smartly react to the varied interests and behaviors of customers. By joining the Loyyal team, you are entering the cutting edge and rapid-changing world of blockchain technology, working collaboratively with a close-knit team to connect the world\u2019s largest loyalty programs. As a member of a Loyyal, you will receive an equity share and market rate salary, as well as gym coverage, company adventures, global travel, and the freedom to have ownership and direction over your work. Of course, medical and 401k benefits too. Responsibilities Loyyal is hiring a Marketing Lead to craft and deliver exceptional content to our current and future customers. The ideal candidate is a self-starter with a strong writing background. You\u2019re a jack-or-jill-of-all-trades who\u2019s excited by the challenge of overseeing all related functions, including Communications and PR. You\u2019re driven to craft inspiring narratives around our product, intellectual property, innovations, partners, clients, challenges, and successes. Own the editorial calendar and work on all types of content, including thought leadership, blog posts, press releases, email marketing, guides, use-case-driven tutorials, articles, social content, and sales enablement materials. Serve as the first line of editorial oversight in Loyyal\u2019s content, ensuring quality and consistency of brand voice across any and all published content Become an expert in understanding the product/project and related specifics on the documentation requirements . Converse with outside agencies and other writers to collaboratively form publications together. Network and maintain industry relationships outside of Loyyal. Develop communication strategies and creative storytelling across tech, industry, and business press Drive the development and execution of PR strategy and initiatives, including media inquiries, interview requests, and additional opportunities Requirements 3+ years of experience developing and implementing Marketing/Communication strategies at high-growth companies Demonstrated passion for and in-depth knowledge of the blockchain space You comprehend and translate complex technical jargon/topics into conversational English and possess a strong command of grammar, spelling, attention to detail, and style. You have the ability to work independently, get tasks done quickly and effectively, and can succeed with little supervision. If you have proven self-edit experience, or have written extensively for industry news style publications, all the better. You excel at interpersonal communication and active listening. You are an avid collaborator that can take an idea and flesh it out. You have a taste for learning and teaching, which make tutorials you write natural and comprehensive. Prior experience working closely with developers or a tech team is a plus. Ability to build and maintain strong relationships with external PR partners Prior experience with at least one CMS, email marketing, and blog platform A cross-functional mindset and experience collaborating across departments When applying please include links to two pieces of content you have written (e.g. white papers, news articles, blogs, website copy, your choice) and say why you choose them as part of your application. Loyyal is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We\u2019re committed to building a diverse and inclusive team. We do not discriminate against qualified employees or applicants because of race, color, religion, gender identity, sex, sexual preference,